<HEAD>Lawyer Jailed for Failing to Pay Fine</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 An attorney who has been absent from the `` Night Stalker'' murder trial of <PERSON> Richard </PERSON> <PERSON> Ramirez </PERSON> was jailed for failing to pay a $ 100 fine for contempt of court. <PERSON> Arturo </PERSON> <PERSON> Hernandez </PERSON> was held Monday in the hospital section of the county's central jail and was to be released today, authorities said. <PERSON> Hernandez </PERSON> stopped representing <PERSON> Ramirez </PERSON> soon after a preliminary hearing. Superior Court Judge <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Tynan </PERSON>, perturbed at his absence, ordered him back to court at one point but later agreed to a daily telephone call from the attorney to see if he was needed. But <PERSON> Hernandez </PERSON> failed to do so, and was fined $ 100, <PERSON> Tynan </PERSON>'s clerk said. The court did n't receive the money. <PERSON> Tynan </PERSON> has since imposed a $ 2,400 fine based on a scale for each day he failed to call. He said <PERSON> Hernandez </PERSON> would be jailed again unless that fine is paid by Sept. 29. <PERSON> Ramirez </PERSON>, 29, is charged with being the devil worshipping killer who invaded <LOCATION> California </LOCATION> homes in a 1985 rampage, killing 13 people. The jury has deliberated for 20 days without a verdict.
