 They had candles and a small gas stove and tried to board up a couple of glass windows,'' said <PERSON> Alamo </PERSON>, whose siblings, parents and grandparents live together in <LOCATION> Bayamon </LOCATION>. `` They live in a cement house but it's always worse in the poorer communities where they live in shacks or wooden houses.''
