said, `` Close the throttles.'' After a few seconds, he called for a right turn and again said, `` Close the throttles.'' But <PERSON> Fitch </PERSON> declined. The board provided no analysis of the taped conversation, which will be used in its continuing investigation into the crash. A report accompanying the transcript noted there was constant discussion among crew members on the best course of action to take during the flight. The transcript shows they discussed whether to lower the landing gear, and later disagreed about when the wheel door was opened. At one point the captain said, `` Anybody got any idea about puttin' the gear down right now?'' Another crew member, identified tentatively as <PERSON> Fitch </PERSON>, later said, `` Dammit. I wish we had n't put that gear down.'' About four minutes before the crash landing, <PERSON> Haynes </PERSON> gave rapid `` back'' and `` forward'' commands and then said, `` Wo n't this be a fun landing?''
