<TEXT>
 They met in a tattoo parlor and the next night she accused him of raping her. Then she hired a lawyer for him and posted his bail, and now they plan to get married. <PERSON> Karen </PERSON> <PERSON> Drake </PERSON> now blames pills given to <PERSON> Donald </PERSON> <PERSON> Farmer </PERSON> the night of the May 24 attack. `` It was n't him,'' Ms. <PERSON> Drake </PERSON> said. `` I've talked to people who know him. And I know him now and he's not the kind of person who would do that. It was a drug-induced stupor the way he acted that night.'' Assistant District Attorney <PERSON> Colleen </PERSON> <PERSON> Marsini </PERSON> moved Monday to dismiss charges in <LOCATION> Delaware </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION>, just outside <LOCATION> Philadelphia </LOCATION>, because Ms. <PERSON> Drake </PERSON> would not testify. `` I think he's using her,'' Ms. <PERSON> Marsini </PERSON> said Tuesday. Ms. <PERSON> Drake </PERSON>, 25, testified in June that she protested when she was `` pinned down'' and raped by Farmer, 31. But on Monday, she said she plans to marry him Sept. 30 in a civil ceremony. `` My mother is not opposed to our marriage. Both of my parents, deep down, love <PERSON> Donnie </PERSON> a lot. And I get along very well with his parents and his two children,'' she said. `` Both <PERSON> Donnie </PERSON> and I have a lot in common,'' she said. `` We're both from <LOCATION> Virginia </LOCATION>, and we both were born in February. While rape and related offenses were withdrawn, Farmer did plead guilty to stealing a diamond ring from Ms. <PERSON> Drake </PERSON> and was placed on two years' probation. Defense attorney <PERSON> David </PERSON> <PERSON> Breen </PERSON> said Ms. <PERSON> Drake </PERSON> hired him June 3 to represent Farmer, two days after Farmer's preliminary hearing on the rape charges. `` She posted bail for him and paid his legal fees. It's the first time I've ever had a victim pay my fee,'' <PERSON> Breen </PERSON> said. Ms. <PERSON> Drak