<LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> to be excessively cautious, for the <ORGANIZATION> White </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> to mistake the status quo for stability.'' The <ORGANIZATION> Democratic </ORGANIZATION> proposal came one day after <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION> Majority Leader <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> Mitchell </PERSON>, <LOCATION> D-Maine </LOCATION>, called the <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> administration's aid package for <LOCATION> Poland </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Hungary </LOCATION> niggardly and urged the president to quickly `` go beyond symbolic nods and meager gestures.''
