nancial officer whose main mission will be to supervise the restructuring of <ORGANIZATION> Campeau </ORGANIZATION>'s retail operations in the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>. The two new executives, who have yet to be selected, will report directly to the board and the restructuring committee. Part of the restructuring includes the sale of the 17-store <ORGANIZATION> Bloomingdale </ORGANIZATION>'s chain, which is part of <PERSON> Federated </PERSON>. <ORGANIZATION> Olympia </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; York will use its `` best efforts'' to arrange temporary financing of about $ 800 million until <ORGANIZATION> Campeau </ORGANIZATION> can arrange for the sale of New York-based <ORGANIZATION> Bloomingdale </ORGANIZATION>'s. <ORGANIZATION> Olympia </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> has agreed to put up some of the bridge loan, if necessary. For coming to <ORGANIZATION> Campeau </ORGANIZATION>'s rescue, <ORGANIZATION> Olympia </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; York will receive warrants entitling it to purchase up to 15.625 million ordinary <ORGANIZATION> Campeau </ORGANIZATION> shares at $ 16 a piece until Sept. 18, 1991. Added to its current 24.5 percent stake in <ORGANIZATION> Campeau </ORGANIZATION>, the purchase of 16 million additional shares would raise <ORGANIZATION> Olympia </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; York's interest in <ORGANIZATION> Campeau </ORGANIZATION> to 38.4 percent, on a fully diluted basis <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> <PERSON> Campeau </PERSON>'s stake would be cut to 43.2 percent from about 54 percent, under the agreement. <ORGANIZATION> Campeau </ORGANIZATION> common stock last traded at $ 13.50 Canadian dollars before it was halted last Wednesday, after trading as high as $ 22.25 a few days earlier. Commenting on the deal with <ORGANIZATION> Olympia </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION>, <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> <PERSON> Campeau </PERSON> said after reviewing projected cash flow requirements and the financial position of <ORGANIZATION> Campeau </ORGANIZATION> and its subsidiaries, he determined that a major restructuring was needed to reduce leverage. `` At my request, <ORGANIZATION> Olympia </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> has agreed to substantially increase its investment in <ORGANIZATION> Campeau </ORGANIZATION> and to be primarily responsible for the refinancing and restructuring,'' <ORGANIZATION> Campeau </ORGANIZATION> said. `` The significant experience and expertise of the <ORGANIZATION> Olympia </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; York organization will greatly assist in the endeavor.''
