ION>, <LOCATION> N.J. </LOCATION>, will feature three contestants trying to answer questions and thereby filling in their `` Trump Card'' _ a box of 15 squares. Prize money for the winners has not yet been determined, <PERSON> Salzman </PERSON> said. The show's host has not been named yet either, although <PERSON> Trump </PERSON> ruled out casino competitor and game show producer <PERSON> Merv </PERSON> <PERSON> Griffin </PERSON>. `` <PERSON> Merv </PERSON> is a friend of mine. <PERSON> Merv </PERSON> is a good guy. He has good game shows. I just happen to have better casinos,'' said <PERSON> Trump </PERSON>.
