<HEAD>Apple Announces Portable Macintosh</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: For release 12:01 a.m. EDT Wednesday; time set by source</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By PETER COY</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Business Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Apple </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Computer </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>'s first portable Macintosh computer is more expensive, bigger and heavier than the latest generation of laptops but the company said Tuesday it makes no compromises on features. Apple hopes to offset the drawbacks of its Macintosh Portable by giving users all the power and features they would get on a full-size Macintosh. `` It's a Macintosh through and through. Now our customers can have Macintosh personal computing anywhere,'' <PERSON> Jean-Louis </PERSON> <PERSON> Gassee </PERSON>, president of <ORGANIZATION> Apple </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Products </ORGANIZATION>, said in a statement. Analysts have been lukewarm toward <ORGANIZATION> Apple </ORGANIZATION>'s first portable. `` I think it'll do well with <ORGANIZATION> Apple </ORGANIZATION>'s existing customer base. I'm not sure it'll gain share in the overall laptop market, though,'' said <PERSON> Bruce </PERSON> <PERSON> Lupatkin </PERSON>, an analyst at <ORGANIZATION> Hambrecht </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; Quist in <LOCATION> San </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Francisco </LOCATION> `` It's a little little big and it's also a little pricey.'' The portable lists at $ 5,799, or $ 6,499 with an optional 40-megabyte hard disk for data storage. A modem for communication over phone lines is extra at $ 449. The weight is 13.7 pounds, or 15.7 pounds with the optional 40-megabyte hard disk. The screen is one-tone rather than color, but is unusually sharp because there is a separate transistor for each screen dot, or picture element. The screen contains more than 250,000 picture elements in a 640 by 400 array, making it 50 percent larger than the screen on a Macintosh SE. To conserve batteries, <ORGANIZATION> Apple </ORGANIZATION> used a version of the Motorola 68000 processor chip that requires 80 percent less power. It also used a low-power kind of memory chip. The lead acid batteries last from six to 12 hours and can be recharged to capacity at any time, <ORGANIZATION> Apple </ORGANIZATION> said. Apple, based in <LOCATION> Cupertino </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Calif. </LOCATION>, also announced the Macintosh IIci, an advanced version of the Macintosh IIcx, which it billed as `` the most powerful Macintosh that <ORGANIZATION> Apple </ORGANIZATION> has ever developed.'' The Macintosh IIci starts at $ 6,269 and ranges up to $ 9,152, putting it in the price range of some computer workstations, machines designed for scientists and engineers. <ORGANIZATION> Apple </ORGANIZATION> said it delivers 55 percent higher performance than the Macintosh IIcx or IIx. It has built-in video capabilities.
