eginning of fiscal 1990 and all Sipco sales were included in the fiscal first quarter. <PERSON> Harper </PERSON> said gains were made in the quarter in all three of <ORGANIZATION> ConAgra </ORGANIZATION>'s basic food industry segments. Consumer frozen foods earnings were up sharply in the largest industry segment, prepared foods. Poultry earnings advanced and operating profit moved up in the fresh red meat business as strong beef processing more than offset weak pork results, the company said. <ORGANIZATION> Tyson </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Foods </ORGANIZATION> assumed control of 20 percent of the domestic poultry market last month with the completion of its $ 1.4 billion merger with <ORGANIZATION> Holly </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Farms </ORGANIZATION>. The buyout followed a takeover struggle for Holly Farms that began last October and pitted Tyson against <ORGANIZATION> ConAgra </ORGANIZATION>.
